            "mimeType": "application/json; charset=UTF-8",
            "size": 985,
            "text": "{\n  \"candidates\": [\n    {\n      \"content\": {\n        \"parts\": [\n          {\n            \"text\": \"**My Process for Getting the Weather in Tokyo**\\n\\nOkay, the user wants the weather for Tokyo. No problem, I can handle this. I know I have a `get_weather` tool at my disposal; that seems like the obvious choice. Now, what does that tool need? Ah yes, I remember, it requires a `city` argument. And the user specifically asked for Tokyo, so the `city` parameter needs to be set to \\\"Tokyo\\\". So, the call should be `default_api.get_weather(city=\\\"Tokyo\\\")`. Easy peasy.\\n\",\n            \"thought\": true\n          },\n          {\n            \"functionCall\": {\n              \"name\": \"get_weather\",\n              \"args\": {\n                \"city\": \"Tokyo\"\n              }\n            },\n            \"thoughtSignature\": \"\"\n          }\n        ],\n        \"role\": \"model\"\n      },\n      \"finishReason\": \"STOP\",\n      \"index\": 0,\n      \"finishMessage\": \"Model generated function call(s).\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"usageMetadata\": {\n    \"promptTokenCount\": 56,\n    \"candidatesTokenCount\": 15,\n    \"totalTokenCount\": 127,\n    \"promptTokensDetails\": [\n      {\n        \"modality\": \"TEXT\",\n        \"tokenCount\": 56\n      }\n    ],\n    \"thoughtsTokenCount\": 56,\n    \"serviceTier\": \"standard\"\n  },\n  \"modelVersion\": \"gemini-2.5-flash\",\n  \"responseId\": \"Fw0VavmLL8X9jrEPyZn9kAw\"\n}\n"
